Hello,

The following submission has been created.

Track Name: Artificial Intelligence and Data Science

Paper ID: 1272

Paper Title: utomating Manual Business Workflows in SaaS Products

Abstract:
SaaS platforms are doing a lot of things manually. Someone has to send the =
task to the person follow up to get it approved run reports and make sure t=
he data is up to date. When the platform is small this is okay.. When it ge=
ts bigger all these manual tasks start to cause problems. There are some to=
ols that can help with this like BPM systems, RPA tools and low-code platfo=
rms.. They do not really work well for SaaS platforms. They were not made f=
or this kind of work. Tools like Zapier and n8n are good for things but the=
y are not good for complicated SaaS workflows. This paper is talking about =
a way to automate SaaS platforms. It is based on rules and events. The syst=
em has five parts: a Workflow Trigger Engine, a Rule Evaluation Module, a P=
laybook Execution Engine, an Integration Layer and a Monitoring and Feedbac=
k Module. To see how well it works we look at three things: how long it tak=
es to do tasks how often there are errors and how many manual tasks are nee=
ded. We compare our system to four tools. We also look at a real case study=
 of a SaaS platform. Run some simulations. The simulations show that our sy=
stem can reduce the time it takes to do tasks by 68-82% reduce errors from =
20-25% to 5-8% and increase the number of tasks that can be done in an hour=
 from 20 to, over 60.

